subSubSection.paragraph:
Female. Similar to male but stouter. Most female specimens with number of small tiny black dots on tegmina (
Fig. 35 A
). On each tegmen brown marking at base and one small brown patch at inner margin at about half length of tegmen. The brown patch midway on the tegmina is lacking in males. Subgenital plate laterally elongated sheathing the ovipositor (
Fig. 39 A
). Ovipositor comparatively short, strongly up-curved, with fine teeth.

